inn1.comm: starts of with a wide down the leg side
loud shout for lbw but turned down. Big inward movement there. It started from just outside off and moved in sharply to hit the pad. Going down leg, though
another inswinger but again goes down the leg side
And again. He is getting some movement and all he has to do is to get the line right. Can he?
Big inswinger again, swings in towards the leg stump to hit the pad. No wonder they chose to bowl here.
he pushes this well outside off and Bagai gathers
full and around the off stump, driven to mid-off
swings in to the middle stump line, worked wide of midwicket
lands outside off on a good length and moves in towards middle, McCullum presses back to punch it to the on side of the pitch
gentle leg cutter outside off stump, left alone
pushes this well outside off and left alone again
extra bounce on this, just outside off, Guptill taps it to left of backward point
sprays this well outside off. Open-chested action and when the left arm doesn't come up as it should, he can end up spraying it
everything is perfect this time: a good-length delivery on the middle and off line, defended to the on side
on the middle stump line, defended of the back foot.
on the off stump line, nudged just wide of the backward point for a single
gets back and across to punch it to mid-off
That typical Baz cut. The back leg goes back and across, and he cuts to third man
lovely inswinger, full in length and moving in to the middle stump line, pushed out to the on side
in the channel outside off stump, left alone
in the zone outside off stump, left alone
Slam! Short and wide and McCullum flays it through point.
lovely delivery: fuller and straightening on the off stump line, McCullum stabs it to backward point
shorter in length, bounces just outside off, McCullum hops to defend to the off
curves away from the off stump, left alone
nagging line and length, on the off stump line, not much room for McCullum to work with and he ends up jabbing it off the inside edge and it bounces past the off stump
on the middle stump line, tapped towards mid-on and they rush across for a quick single
Whack. it wasn't all that short and McCullum opened his stance and went for the pull and it raced away to the left of mid-on
full and outside off, left alone
fuller, swinging in, McCullum makes an effort to stretch forward, get outside the off stump line, and turns it to midwicket
swings in to the middle stump line, squirted behind square-leg
leans forward to drive to mid-off
gets back to punch this one out to cover
short and wide and McCullum whacks it through cover point. He blasted that
on the off stump line, pushed to the on side
supah delivery: It landed on a good length outside off and shaped away, McCullum felt for it, bat away from the body and the ball rushed past the edge
wider and McCullum chases it but can't reach it
leans across to push a length delivery wide of cover for a single
Booming off drive. Guptill glides forward to cover for the away swing and creams this full delivery to left of mid-off
Boom. It was slightly short in length and McCullum moved so quickly into position to unfurl a stylish pull
well outside off but again McCullum moves quickly - that back leg moved back and across really swiftly - to carve it to deep backward point
fuller and straighter, driven back to the bowler
on the middle stump line, tapped to the leg side
leans forward to defend to the off side
Guptill unfurls one of his characteristic lovely lofted drives to the straight boundary. He leaned forward to lift this high over mid-on. Nice fluent swing of the bat.
in the zone outside the off stump, the batsman is beaten, pushing inside the line
length delivery that straightens on the middle and off line, jabbed to the on side
Blast! McCullum rushes down the track, moves outside leg in the process and whacks this length delivery over long-off
shout for lbw. It landed on a length around middle and tilted in towards the leg stump to hit the pad. Hawk eye says it would have clipped the outside of leg stump
in the zone outside off, beaten on the froward prod and Bagai is quick to collect and break the stumps
full delivery and McCullum edges the drive to third man boundary
pushes this wide outside off stump
in the zone outside off, left alone
in the channel outside off, left alone
goes for another of his lofted off drives but ends up slicing it to wide long-off
drops this short and Guptill shows he is not all about lofting to the straight boundary; he swivels to unfurl a cracking pull
in the corridor outside off, left alone
just outside the off stump, defended to the off
works this behind square-leg for a single
full in length on the middle stump line, defended on the front foot
leans forward to drive to mid-off
glides forward to defend this to the leg side

Wonderful Ashish Bagai! What a keeper! He was standing up to the stumps and takes a loverly catch. Guptill got the edge on the defensive prod and Bagai moved his hands quickly to cover the deviation. Good delivery too; it landed on a good length and just about cut away a bit
In the zone outside off and Bagai, now standing back, collects
length delivery well outside off and McCullum freed his arms. He went after it and the ball flew off the edge to third man boundary
fuller, straighter, pushed back to the bowler
Whacikty whack. Baz glides across to slam this up and over cover
leans forward to push it to mid-off
stays back to tap this to midwicket region for a single
Whack. short and wide, McCullum reaches out to carve it to the point boundary.
gets forward to push it back down the track
works this wide of midwicket for a single
Lash em Ryder! He reaches outside off and slashes a full delivery well outside off past backward point
full and around the off stump line, edged to point
tries the bouncer, climbs chest-high. So far so good. Blink. Ryder crash-pulls it to the square-leg boundary.
overpitches this one on the legs, flicked away to deep square-leg
moves forward and plays an aerial off drive but through the gap in the wide mid-off region. It races away.
leans well forward to steer it to point
gets back and across to steer it to third man region. That's his 50 20th ODI fifty. fifty from 38 balls. Canada! Be worried, very worried!
leans forward to push it to backward point
stays back to dab it to midwicket
short and bouncing outside off, Baz is beaten on the cut
in the zone outside off, Ryder hits it hard but can't pierce the off-side field
stays back to push it to the off
stays back to defend to the off side
in the channel outside off, Ryder tries to cut but makes no contact
just outside off stump, run down to third man
on the middle and leg, pushed out to the on side .. rolls of the pad actually
stays back to punch it to the off side
around the off stump line, late cut to third man for couple for runs
goes hard at this and ends up dragging it to midwicket
just outside the off stump, run down to third man
short in length and outside off stump, McCullum went back and across to play a cracking cut shot. He moves so quickly, like a boxer
fuller, mcCullum goes too hard at the ball and ends up dragging it to the leg side
back of a length outside off and angling across Ryder who leaves
closer to off stump this time, Ryder defends to off stump.
short of a length this time outside off, steered through to third man for a single
shorter on off stump, Baz stays back and defends down the track
looks to cut a fullish ball just outside off, and doesn't make contact
closer to off stump to end the over, Baz gets behind the line quietly and defends
drops too short outside off, Ryder under-edges the pull into the ground and misses out.
turns into the pads, Ryder hangs back and tucks it square for a single
short of a length and turning in from leg stump, Baz works against the spin for one through square leg. Some turn for Rao straight away.
tossed up on off, Ryder leans out and smothers the spin and works it to the leg side
Ryder misses out again, flighted outside leg and he sweeps straight to short fine leg who misfields ... and they still get a run. It was the wrong 'un from Rao.
holds the length back and gets it to go away from Baz who check drives to the off side
short of a length outside off, Ryder stands back and cracks a cut into the covers
Baz hangs back and steers a back of length ball on leg stump into the covers for one more
marginally short of a length this time, Ryder looks to pull immediately but its not short enough for him to truly pummel. Single to midwicket
tighter length on off, Baz stands on the crease and punches with the full face to mid on for a single

huge lbw appeal turned down ... Baidwan and Cheema discuss and decide to not review it. Back of a length on leg stump, and then it straightens to head towards the outer half of leg stump, so a review would have been wasted. Plus, there seemed to have been an inside edge. Though, in the absence of HotSpot that would have been tough to establish.
fuller length ball on a similar line, Ryder tries to hang back and slam it over midwicket. Straight to the fielder and he gets a single
flight on off stump, Ryder pushes him into the off side. Rip and inward turn.
holds it back this time, Ryder picks the spin and plays carefully to the leg side for one
Baz leans out confidently to the flight and eases wide of extra cover for another single
back of a length on the stumps, Ryder tucks quietly to the leg side for one more
there are more singles here than in a singles bar. Baz pushes another one to long off as Rao flights on the stumps.
fullish on middle, Ryder flicks off the front foot to midwicket
single to the leg side for Baz as he leans out and nudges against the spin
Ryder looks to chip inside out, but finds extra cover with a nicely timed stroke
turn for Davison from middle, from round the wicket, Ryder covers the line and defends
fuller on middle and leg, worked on the bounce to midwicket
quicker one, at 93 kph, fired in flatter and goes straight on. Ryder misses the backfoot flick
ends the over with a single as he guides Davison into the covers with the spin
tossed up on leg stump, swept away to deep midwicket for a single
googly flighted outside off, Baz seemed to pick it as he reached out and dabbed into the off side
over-pitched but very straight, Baz digs it out straight back at Rao
Baz lunges out to the pitch and steers quietly to the off side.
Baz gets the single this time, driving assertively past cover after moving forward to the flight of another Rao leggie
back of a length on off to finish, Ryder defends down the track

a boundary after a long time. Baz plays that reverse sweep of it, and did not look like he was in any kind of risk playing it. Reaches out as if he wants to cover drive, even as he changes the grip and slaps the ball on its way to third man
flighted on off, Baz drives into the covers for a single
Ryder is being quite careful here, he wants a big one. Defends a back of length ball into the covers
now he gets the single, hanging back to a short ball and cutting fine
Baz reaches across to cover the line and defends Davison down the track
landed outside off and straightening, Baz again stoutly defends to the off side
short ball, breaking back into Ryder who punches against the spin to cover for one

flight and drift onto leg stump, Baz sweeps straight to short fine leg where Osinde misfields. They think of a single, start, stop, speculate the absurdities of life, think again, start and are getting set for a horrible mix up before Baz runs back in. Just in time.
defends a flighted ball down the track

Baz has tonked Rao out of the ground with a typically cavalier inside out off drive with the spin. He runs out of the crease, gets inside the line and unleashes those tattooed fore-arms through the line. Drilled out of the ground.
short of a length, wisely so from Rao, McCullum stays back and works him to midwicket
single to end the over, Baz stays back and works it to midwicket to retain strike
short but cramping Baz for room as he tries to force against the spin. He finds cover.
speared in on the pads, worked with the spin to midwicket
Baz reaches out to the flight and drives into the covers to get the single away
Ryder works a single into the covers, calmly handing it back to Baz
Baz works another single to the leg side as Davison turns one in.
full on leg stump, Ryder can't find the length to play the sweep, but tries nevertheless, and misses.
flighted on off and breaking away, eased into the covers.
he gets the single this time, working into the covers past the fielder. Baz has set his sights on a real big one today. And Canada are not really trying to stop him.

the pudgy sweep that has the Ryder trademark on it. Leans that front foot out to the pitch and then comes down hard on a flighted ball. One instant later, the ball has scurried past the deep square leg fence.
shortens the length this time on off stump, Ryder plays with the spin to the leg side
flat and quick again, Ryder defends with the spin to the on side
this time Ryder jumps inside the line and clips a single through square leg to bring up the 25-overs mark in good stead for NZ.

dropped at cover. Not helping Canada's cause. Davison tosses up on off, Ryder looks to smash the cover drive and goes uppishly. Surkari had to tumble forward and to the left to get to it, and he managed to. But as he tumbled, the ball went tumbling out of the hand as well.
flat on middle and off, played cautiously in front of the wicket
clip0s this time with the angle to the leg side, still not for runs
now Davison gets the single, driving with the spin past covers for one
ends with one on the pads, Baz chips it with the spin to midwicket for one more
shortish ball outside off, Baz looks to cut and can't time it

over-pitched wide outside off, Baz needs no second invitation to go after it with a vengeance. He did not middle it, but swung so hard that the outside edge flew very fine through third man for another 4.

Huge appeal for caught behind, but is Bagai going to review it? He hasn't reviewed it. This is interesting. Short of a length outside off, McCullum looked to get across and cut it away, but did not middle it. Sure noise as the ball passes him, but replays indicate it was the bat hitting the pad. Bagai went up immediately, but chose not to review it. He probably had an inkling. Or he knows the odds of getting a positive review on an edge is low when there is no HotSpot.
fuller on off stump, Baz drives cleanly into the covers for a couple
Baz covers the line on off stump and defends sedately down the track
Baz hangs back on off stump and gets the steer past point for a single
short of a length on off stump, Baz stays back and defends to the leg side
on off stump this time, Baz is again sedate in defence as he dinks it to cover point
that one stopped on him as Davison threw it up on middle and off, worked to the leg side a little uppishly
fired in quicker on off stump, Baz defends down the track
another dot. Speared on the pads, and Baz flicks straight to short fine leg
Davison gets a maiden out of nowhere, Baz reaches out and smothers the spin to defend down the track
full length ball on Ryder's off stump and he defends into the off side

this Bagai is among the best keepers in the World Cup. And surely the best investment banker who is also a keeper. Wide and quick from Chohan, Baz misses the cut, but Bagai collects without a problem, and even whips the bails off
fuller on off stump, Baz drives through extra cover and moves to 89.
short of a length and tight on off stump, Ryder looks to steer but can't get it away off the square
back of a length this time, Ryder forces into the covers without hitting it too hard and gets a couple to deep extra cover
short of a length on off stump to end the over, driven into the covers for another single
tossed up on off, Ryder defends carefully down the track

Ryder has seen the suicide button, and pressed it with glee. A 100 for the taking against this dawdle of a Canadian attack, and he's let the opportunity go after doing the hard work. Ryder tosses it up on the off stump, Ryder gets under it and then is not sure just how hard to hit it. He plays a half-hearted chip in the end, and sends it straight to long on. He is livid, and smashes his pads on the way back. That wasn't a long boundary either.
tossed up on leg stump, Baz goes on and on, working down to wide mid on for one more.
leans out to the pitch and guides with an angled face towards point. Baz wants the strike and hares down the track, Taylor looks at him incredulously.
loopy delivery on middle and off, Taylor works to midwicket with the spin
Taylor is away, easing a flighted ball, past mid on for a single
he spears the first ball down the leg side. Wide called.
full delivery on off stump, Taylor guides into the off side after reaching out
back of a length on off stump, careful check drive into the covers
over-pitched and slanting down the leg side, Baz drives down to long on for a single
short of a length on off stump, Taylor hangs back on the crease and defends to the off side as it jumps up. Decent carry.
short of a length outside off, Taylor gets beside the line and cracks the cut to deep backward point where there's a sliding stop.
oho, Baz needlessly wanders out of the crease after flicking straight to short fine leg. Second time that's happened, he was nowhere in the scene when the throw came in. But it missed.
Taylor eases a single down the ground
Baz looks for the reverse sweep, doesn't time it but gets a single in front of square since he was early into the shot
Taylor works Davison with the spin for another single to mid on
Baz stays on the crease to a short of length ball and clips through midwicket for another single
flat and quick on middle and off, Taylor drives straight to mid on
Taylor brings up the second drinks break, working a single to the off side
full length on off stump, Taylor leans out and defends to the off side

bosh. I wonder if Osinde was seeing what Taylor did to Pakistan. If he had, he'd know that full on the leg stump is not the best ball to bowl at Taylor. And when you do, he'll just tonk you like that, off the pads, with a fierce whiplash through midwicket
Osinde's not learning fast enough. Another one too straight, coming in with the angle, and flicked through midwicket for four more
back of a length on leg stump, Taylor tucks it backward of square for one
over-pitched on off stump, driven down the ground for a single
slower ball, ends up as a gift on the leg stump and Taylor works down to long on for one.
gets forward to defend to the on
brings up his 4000 ODi runs with a hit to deep midwicket. He is very close to overhauling SRT!
pushes this to the off for a single
slightly short of length, mistimes the cut to cover point
on the off stump line, from round the stumps, turned to the leg side
works this wide of the midwicket fielder for a single
on the pads, worked behind square-leg
turns away from the off, cut away to backward point
slider on the pads, clipped to backward square-leg for a single
gets back to punch it to long-on
lovely delivery, slower, bit more air, dipping outside off and Taylor reaches out and ends up almost scooping it to cover
stays back to dab this to backward point
gets forward and across to defend
around the off stump line, nudged to the cover region
turns in to the middle and off line, moves to 99 with a wristy dab past square-leg
rotates the strike with a nurdle behind square-leg
stays back, opens the bat-face and pushes it to point. That's his 100 His wife and son cheer from the stands. Third ODI ton. Will he unleash hell in the batting Powerplay?

goes for the sweep but is struck on the pad outside off. Or so it seemed. Canada go for the DRS. The ball landed on the middle and off and hit him in front of off stump. Hawk eye says it would have clipped the outside of the off stump. On-field call. Not out is the verdict
charges out for the big hit but he mistimes the flat-batted hit and edges to the leg side
walks forward to drive to the on side
fetches it from outside off and slams it to deep midwicket
Batting Powerplay has taken its first wicket. Full in length and outside off, Baz slams it straight to extra cover. Fine innings, but its over now
a high bouncer and Nathan ducks
short of length outside off, dabbed to point
gets forward to drive it back down the track
full in length outside off, steered straight to backward point
The fine-leg is up inside the circle and he serves a full toss outside leg. Taylor flicks it to the recycle bin
good-length delivery on the middle, pushed to through mid-on
full in length outside off stump, driven through mid-off
short in length around off stump, swatted past midwicket

Whack! It was the bouncer around off stump and Taylor pulls it to deep midwicket where Davison ran in too much, misjudged it and the ball sailed over him. Had he stayed near the ropes, he could have got it
Another short ball. Blink. Pull. The ball is thrown back from the wide midwicket boundary
fuller, around off stump, dug out back down the track
The six-orgy (read it again, no typos!) begins. It was a poor short ball and Taylor thrashes it over square-leg boundary

Drama! Taylor fetches a slower one and heaves it high towards long-on. Cheema back-pedaled and as he caught the ball, his back foot touched the boundary line. He threw it back in the field of play but the damage was done.
Taylor has gone berserk here. And without the help of Kamran Akmal. Baidwan chokes and serves a low full toss outside off and Taylor has creamed it through covers
backs away the leg stump line, the bowler follows, swing and a miss and they get a bye
full delivery on the middle, swiped to short fine-leg fielder
Crash bang. Nathan moves outside leg stump and smashed this length delivery over mid-off
fuller, driven to extra cover for a quick single
full pitched on the pads, flicked away past square-leg

A beamer! accidental. A high full toss from round the stumps, Taylor tries to pull but gets away from the line of fire and Bagai, standing up to the stumps, puts his left hand to make a half-stop. Cheema apologizes
Low full toss on the leg stump line and Taylor  cues up and swings it over backward square-leg boundary
moves outside leg, Balaji gets the leg break to turn in to the middle stump line, Nathan forces it over cover
Shout for lbw turned down. that looked close. It landed on the leg and middle and turned past the attempted sweep shot to hit the pad. No replays in yet
Pressure. immense pressure. Balaji drags this slider short and on the leg stump line, Taylor pulls it away in disdain
Who is going to stop Rosco? He glides forward, fetches the leg break from the middle stump line and drags it through wide mid-on
And they get the yips. Bala slips this wide down the leg side and even Bagai can't shuffle across in time

Bala strikes with a lovely delivery. It was a flighted leg break on a good length around off and middle. Brave delivery. Correct delivery. Rosco goes for the big hit down the ground but the ball turns and he gets the edge. Hansra moved forward from backward point and dived forward to take a good catch. The Rosco show is over.
gets back to clip this to the on side for a single
low dipping full toss, eased back to the bowler
Dropped by the bowler. It was a dolly. It was a flighted delivery that dipped on Kane who ended up scooping it shoulder high to the right of the bowler who clanged it.
gets forward to push it to the on side
leans forward to drive it back to the bowler
around off stump line, steered through covers
on the middle and leg, squirted to square-leg. Overthrows at the non-striker's end as the bowler didn't expect a throw would come in at his end and had turned his back.

Balaji gives us another lovely dismissal. A flighted loopy dipping leg break that drifted towards leg, luring Nathan to try playing it to the leg and the turn forces him to get a leading edge. Balaji lunges to his right to pouch that. A classic leggie's wicket. Lovely drift there
gets forward to defend
flighted around off, driven to long-off
just outside off, skids away, cut to point
fetches it from outside off and sweeps it for a single
spins from outside leg, dabbed to midwicket region
Catch it was the cry as Styris whips it aerially, just wide of the diving midwicket
gets forward to push it to the on side of the pitch
quicker, on the middle and leg, nudged to midwicket
goes on with the arm, from round the stumps, just outside off, dabbed to the leg side
looks to slog sweep, the ball is too full, and he ends up stabbing it down the track
around off, cut away to sweeper cover
Balaji continues to tease. Kane goes down the track but is unable to reach the pitch as the leg break dips on him and he edges the drive to point
Catch dropped! Balaji is fuming! Kane went back and punched it straight to short extra cover where Baidwan let it go under his hands and right between his legs! What a clanger!
works this one away for a single
gets back to clip this one past square-leg
delicious leg break that breaks away past the attempted cut. Bagai takes it
this one slides to the pads and rolls away for a leg bye
Styris goes downtown. He went down his knee, cleared his front foot and swung this full delivery over long-on
works this past square-leg for a single
backs away to cut it through covers. Overthrows at the striker's end
gets forward to ping long-on
Good bye! Styris unleashes hell on a bent knee. This one is a slog sweep and it flies over midwicket boundary
drives through the on side for a single
gets forward to drive this to long-on
flighted leg break, again dips rapidly on Kane who can't reach the pitch of the ball but goes through with his shot to long-on
moves outside leg, Balaji hurls it quicker, forced away to sweeper cover
leg break on the middle stump line, swept away for a single
Adrenalin rush! Styris rushes down the track and smashes this leg break to wide long-off boundary
goes down the track again but Balaji pushes this to the pads, cramps him for room, and it rolls away of the pad
shuffles across, a low full toss on the leg stump arrives and Kane helps it along to the fine-leg boundary
The back-of-hand slower one and for a moment I thought Kane has hit mishit it to deep midwicket. He slog sweeps it to wide midwicket boundary
walks across to the off, and steers the length delivery through point. More overthrows. It should have been two but they have leaked an extra run
Fabulicious straight hit. Scotty clears the front foot and lofts it to the straight boundary.
a slower one, back of the hand stuff again, just outside off and on a good length. Styris moved outside leg and carved it over backward point
Styris falls to a full toss. He swings it towards long-on where Davison moves in to take a good low catch, lunging forward
Kane lashes this full toss to the midwicket boundary. The runs are coming in a flood here
paddles this one to fine-leg region
squirts this through to deep square-leg region
yorker on the middle stump line, dug out through midwicket
a dipping slower one, Kane checks his shot and pushes it through the off side
Another slower one and Kane is too early into his slog sweep. He will get a bye, though
short in length on the middle, swatted away to deep square-leg
Massive! 10th six of the game. Highest in this WC. Franklin clobbers a full pitched delivery into the stands beyond long-on
Huge!  Another gentle full delivery, angling in and Franklin lifts this over wide midwicket boundary
Another full delivery in the slot and Franklin crashes it over covers. Whoa!
This is humongous!  Monster hit. In the slot, a length delivery and Franklin has absolutely tonked it over long-on.
High full toss, a no ball, and Franklin edges the intended swat-pull to third man boundary. Hell unleashed!
Oh dear... he sprays a wide outside off stump.
Not a four. not a six. Just couple of runs. what's the world coming to? Franklin drives to long-off for two runs.

inn2.comm: Mills lands the first one full on off stump and gets it to nip in, it is defended down the track
Ruvindu winds up and swings, ends up looking like the icons on Fantasy Cricket for the batsmen. He misses though as Mills angles across him.
Ruvindu is away, driving a full ball cleanly past the bowler for a couple
short of a length on off stump, Ruvindu reaches across and defends to the off side
back of a length outside off, defended into the offside after getting half across
positive cricket from Ruvindu, might as well go after this. Short of a length at 134 kph and going across, he tries to pull and times it well. Straight to mid on, though.
full ball on leg stump, clipped uncertainly into the leg side, where midwicket fields
Patel covers the line as Southee keeps it short of a length and defends to the offside
fuller length, pleasing feet movement from Patel as he leans into an upright drive down the track

it's cruel to term it that, but Southee has dropped Patel. Length ball on off stump, it's there to be driven and Hiral goes at it hard. Southee on his follow through tries to tumble to his left and catch, but it's past him in a flash though he gets a hand to it
that man Guptill, prowls away on the off side, as Hiral smashes on the up. Guptill dives away to his left and collects
ends with one short of a length on middle and off and Patel drives solidly to mid on

Ross Taylor is here, Ross Taylor is there, Ross Taylor is almost everywhere. Full delivery, angled across looking for the outside edge that will keep the slips interested, but not this kind of an edge. Ruvindu flashes at it with furious anger and gets the healthiest of outside edges that seems set to take it over the slips and through to third man. Someone forgot to tell Rossco, jumping up with his right hand stretched up. He plucked it at it's peak as if he were reaping mango harvest. Delicious. The timing of the jump was outstanding.
Back of a length on off stump, defended into the off side off the back foot.
wider outside off this time, Surkari lets it go through
just the kind of jaffa Mills excels in producing. Lands on a length, jumps up disconcertingly and nips off. Surkari does well not to get a touch.
fuller and angling in from wider of the crease, Surkari shoulders arms
nothing poke outside off, Mills gets another one to dangle around off stump and hold its line, Surkari feels for it with an angled blade.
back of a length around off stump, Patel covers the line and defends down the track
that wasn't far from nailing him. Southee gets the inducker to swerve in menacingly and Patel goes for an ambitious flick around the pads. Managed to get an inside edge to the leg side
shortens the length on leg stump, it is nudged to the leg side for a single
fuller length on off stump, Surkari presses across and defends to the off side
that's a good bouncer, clocks in at 132 kph but is not too short, and Surkari weaves away wisely
length ball on off stump, Surkari eases into a defensive push to the off side
length ball outside off, Surkari allows it through to the keeper
draws him out with a fuller length ball, Surkari is a little late to come forward but defends down the track

Mills has another. Catching practice this time for Rossco. Not the first time Surkari has gone fishing outside off stump with an angled bat after getting half across, and that too very late. This angler hooks no salmon, no trout, no sardines, no nothing. Instead he gets Taylor. Easy catch at waist height, taken without any fuss.
back of a length and coming in at 131 kph from outside off, Bagai hangs back and gingerly defends to the off side
horrific loosener, short, wide and sitting up like a pie. Bagai lays into it, cracking an airy cut over the infield for the first boundary
and now the second, this time Ryder sprays it on the pads and Bagai tickles it along to fine leg for four more.
length ball on middle and leg, driven to mid on off the front foot

Patel puts the 'no' in nothing shot. Back of a length ball outside off, Patel pushes his front foot forward by approximately six inches and waves the bat at the general line of the ball. In hope. No contact made.
better, plays with a straight bat and pushes a length ball to mid off
another lively bouncer from Southee, this time at 140 kph, and Patel arches back to stay out of harm's way
swiped away. For once Southee loses the line and angles this into middle and leg, Patel plonks the front foot across and tonks across the line, over midwicket for four.
141 kph, Southee tries an inswinging yorker and it nearly pays off as Patel has another ambitious swish to the leg side. It took a bit of the bottom edge and ran away to the slips.
poor start, gentle loosener on leg stump and he's immediately wincing in disappointment as Bagai flicks him cleanly through midwicket
top delivery to come  back, Oram holds the length back, changes the line to off stump and gets the leg cutter to dart away past the outside edge
again, a touch of away movement as Bagai reaches out to defend to point
over-pitched on leg stump, and Bagai plays a crisp on-drive dead straight to mid on
short of a length outside off, Bagai pushes outside the line of off stump and leaves
yorker on off stump at 130 kph, good finish to the over after that four. Bagai digs it out to mid on
short of a length and on the pads, Patel nudges to square leg and takes off for a suicidal single. Bagai sends him back and he dives in frantically, as How misses the under-arm flick
nice rhythm from Southee, 137 kph on off stump and it is defended back down the track
hmm, ugly from Patel again. Tries to heave away a short of length ball outside off stump through the covers. He didn't have any chance of getting that away/
Patel gets four, only just. Short ball, hustles him into a completely out of position pull, and the top edge just goes over a leaping Brendon McCullum

whoa, Patel pulls off one of those booming carves over the off side. Some shot that, not many can play it, in essence a pull over the covers. Short of a length, not there for the drive or the cut, he just sets up a solid base and spanks it over the infield, the backlift starting at third man and the follow through ending at midwicket
even better this time, Patel's feet move forward to a length ball and he just slams it on the up over wide mid off. Majestic.
angling into Bagai, who looks to tuck a single to the leg side, but can't get it away
half an appeal from Oram as he hits Bagai above the pads, the batsman missing another flick. Too high and going down the leg side
short of a length outside off, Bagai taps to cover point and refuses the single
fuller length on middle and off, played back down the track cautiously
short of a length outside off and steered from the crease towards point
fuller length on off stump, he draws him into the drive to the off side
starts off with a no-ball, full and swinging away. But he's over-stepped.

he's hammered the free-hit into the adjoining maidan. Almost. Franklin tries the bouncer, at his pace it is a bit of a joke really, Patel stays under it and whacks the pull shot over deep backward square leg. That bumper had neither pace nor direction going for it.
better length, and more importantly, not a no ball. Defended.
fuller on middle and off, Patel thumps the drive back hard and Franklin cleans up on his follow through.
back of a length outside off, Patel dabs a single to point
Bagai seeks a single, looking to drop into the off side and take off. The ball goes nowhere.
length ball on middle stump to end the over, defended back down the track by a crease-bound Bagai.
short ball, aimed at the head and he backs out of the opportunistic pull at the last moment
slow bouncer, Patel gets into no position as he tries to steer to the off side and gets it away airily backward of point
length ball on off stump, Bagai looks to play to the off side, but can't get it away for runs.
length ball on off stump again, closer to the batsman and Bagai plays back down the track
fuller ball on a length and defended down the track
this one comes in with the angle and Bagai works it to the leg side. Can't get it past mid on
back of a length on off stump and defended off the back foot into the off side
Bagai gets a single, works this ball to the leg side for a single

how's he doing this? This Patel has this trademark off side thump to balls that aren't full or fast. He's either good at golf, or he's a huge fan of Sanath Jayasuriya. Just stands beside the line and frees his arms through the line. Timed superbly.
and he gets a single now, pushing in front of square for a single
Bagai gets a couple, steering with control through point as Franklin offers rare width outside off
fuller length ball outside off, Patel plays a check drive to the off side
whoa, another one of those bouncers, Patel doesn't try to pull as much as get under it and whack the leather off the ball. Doesn't make contact.

Has he edged it this time? NZ review an appeal for caught behind that's been turned down. Another short one from Oram, this one just outside off and Patel again goes for a vicious pull, despite not having the room. There was a sure noise as the ball passed the bat. No other technology to aid in this review. It's eventually been given out.
length ball comes into the pads, he works it to the leg side
he leans out across and steers with an opened face into the off side for one
fuller length outside off and defended into the off side off the front foot
Franklin eases one past Hansra as he he look to leave outside off
he leans across to the line of off stump and steers through covers, but not for runs
short of a length on off stump, Hansra jumps up to cover the bounce and defends to the off side
fuller length outside off, Hansra is off to a quiet but compact start as he defends again into the covers, and gets a single this time
slowish offcutter that comes very late and Bagai can't time the forced dab
that's one of the most productive scoring areas today. Bagai looks to pull and fast short ball and top-edges over the keeper's head.
length ball outside off, he eases into the steered drive to third man.
short of a length ball outside off, cracks the cut straight to cover
whoa, that's a robust outside edge as Bagai goes for the cut to a ball well outside off and gets it down to third man
Hansra explores the aerial route, whiplashing a ball on the pads high over vacant midwicket for a couple
another outside egde, this time for Hansra as he looks to carve over the off side, and gets it away between widish gully and slip
full length ball angling across Hansra who plays off the front foot into the covers
shortens the length outside off, he covers the line and defends into the off side.
shortish ball, angles into the pads and is whipped through midwicket for a single
Franklin comes round the wicket and bowls the most harmless fulltoss you will see on off stump, and it is duly whacked through the covers for four
shorter this time, and some away nip, Bagai guides to third man for a single
fullish ball outside off, steered to third man for one more.
on the off stump line, nudged back down the track
juicy full toss but no free gifts for me says the batsman who quietly taps it to cover
gets forward to ease this down to long-on
turns in to the middle and off line, pushed to mid-on
Classy hit. It was a flighted delivery around off, he gave himself some room and lofted it inside-out over covers
full, really full, jabbed behind square-leg for a single
off cutter, as ever, from Styris, punched out to cover
on the pads, tucked away through backward square-leg
cuts down the leg side, past the waft and McCullum moves very quickly to whip off the bails in a flash. The umpire refers it to third umpire but the back foot was inside
on the middle stump line, pushed out to straightish short midwicket
lunges across to jab it of the bat and the pad to the off
on the off and middle line, another off cutter, pushed back to Styris
full on the middle stump line, nudged to the leg side
leans forward to drive to long-off
presses back to defend this to the on side
stretches forward to drive it back to the bowler
slower, just outside off, driven down to long-off
Almost carried to short midwicket. Bagai whipped it just short of Taylor
gets forward to push it back down the track
off cutter on the off and middle line. pushed to the on side
this time he pushes it past the non striker but short midwicket intervenes
on the pads, clipped behind square-leg
cuts in towards the pads again, and yet another single behind square leg
works this past the diving backward square-leg fielder
fuller, around off stump line, leans forward to defend
gets back to wrist this to backward square-leg
presses back to push it back to the bowler
gets this down to long-on for a single.
leans well forward to push it back to the bowler
takes a couple of steps down the track and on drives to long-on
jabs this uppishly but short of the bowler. He was trying to push it to cover
gets forward to force this down to long-on
taps this vacant spaces at cover point for another jogged single
on the off stump line, pushed back to the bowler
slower, drifting down the legs, full and he flicks it down to fine-leg region where Oram makes a tumbling stop
gets forward to push this one away
on the pads again, glanced down to fine-leg region
leans well forward to ease it to long-on
flighted around off, pushed out to the off side
spins in from outside off, Hansra drove outside the line and edges it to the on side
stretches well forward to dab this back to the bowler
on the off stump line, worked past square-leg for a single
in the zone outside off stump, Hansra tries to cut but doesn't connect
And again. Hmm ...
fullish delivery, tilting in late, jabbed away to midwicket
short in length around off, Bagai stays on the leg stump line and cuts hard but can't beat point
homing in on the middle, defended to the on side
straightens on the off stump line, pushed out to cover
leans forward to defend to the off
turns in the middle, dabbed to the leg side
tossed up on a length outside off, driven to long-off
rushes down the track and lofts to long-off where Oram moves to his right to make a fine diving stop
moves outside leg and goes for a big off drive but edges it through the vacant slip region
gets outside leg again and this time cuts to deep backward point
cuts in to the middle and off line, defended to the off side
a sharp bouncer and it flies over left shoulder
leans forward to push a length delivery to the bowler who fires it back at the striker's end
from round the stumps now, full and on the middle, driven to mid-off
Whoa! Hansra has woken up. Good shot too. He moved forward and smashed a length delivery from the off stump right over the bowler
back over the stumps now. full in length on the middle, pushed to mid-on for a quick single
from round the stumps, floated just outside off, edged to square-leg
leans forward to push-drive to the on side
leans forward to tuck this behind square-leg
moves down the track and pings long-off
tossed full outside off and Bagai crashes it to the cover boundary. 50 for Bagai. Good brisk innings.  A fab keeper and now showing his batting prowess
pushes this through covers for a single
overpitched delivery on the legs, flicked away for a single
full delivery around off, on driven to long-on
on the middle and leg, tucked to short midwicket
on the middle and off, steered to backward point
just outside the off stump, cut away to deep point
leans forward to defend to the on side
gets outside leg and dabs to backward point
backs away again and this time cuts hard to deep point
The paddle scoop! He reached across outside off and scooped it over leg slip region
gets forward to nudge this to midwicket
moves outside leg and pushes this quietly to the off
just outside off, carved through covers for two runs
Big hit. He cleared the front foot and heaved this full delivery to wide midwicket boundary
on thye off and middle line, pushed to backward point and after some hesitation, he gets across in time
full delivery on the leg stump line, pushed out to cover for a single
slower one, full toss, hit down to long-on
moved outside leg stump and whacked a flighted delivery around off to the extra cover boundary
gets forward to turn this to the leg side
dabs this to short fine-leg region for a single
on the pads, flicked to square-leg region
gets forward to dab this to short midwicket
moves towards leg, the ball is on the leg stump line, stabbed to short third man
just outside the off stump, again steered to short third man
moves outside leg to try create room, and cuts the ball from the middle stump line to backward point
on the off stump line, defended to the bowler
full and straight, rotates the strike with a push-drive towards long-on
off cutter on the middle stump line, punched to cover
from round the stumps, full delivery on the pads, worked past square-leg
gets outside leg and has a big swing at it but edges this behind square-leg. Kane followed him there
leans forward to drive it back to the bowler
pushes this down the leg side, quickish, and neither the batsman or the keeper can get to it
on the pads, nurdled behind square
again for the nth time moves outside leg and slices it to deep cover
drifts onto pads and Bagai clips through square leg for one
slow offcutter, Hansra gets across and flicks to midwicket
good shot, over-pitched on off stump and driven fluently into the covers
is Bagai going to have a tilt at this? Over-pitched outside off, and he lofts it aerially to wide long off
short of a length on off stump, worked back down the track
full and on the pads, driven down to long on for one.
flighted on off stump, he leans out and drives to mid on
Bagai looks to loft Nathan over long off, but the timing is poor and it lands well short of the fielder
on the pads, Hansra taps through square leg for one
nicely done, Bagai makes room and steers the cut fine before haring back for a second. He is down now with a cramp.
Bagai keeps clearing away and having a go down the track, but Nathan keeps it too full for him to truly loft and he gets a single to long off.
this one is worked to the leg side with the spin
short of a length just outside off, Bagai tries to steer to third man, but under edges just side of the keeper
short of a length outside off, and he cuts backward of point for one more
slow offcutter on off, driven back to the bowler
Styris holds it back and it is dabbed in front of point for a single
swish and a miss outside off as Styris keeps nagging away at a boringly irritating pace.
Bagai ends the over with a flourish, getting outside leg and flicking an offcutter than ended on the pads expertly, finer than deep backward square leg. 189 reqd off 84.
angling in back of a length and worked to midwicket for a single
Bagai's hitting them too straight. He's smashed the leather off this one and hit the non-striker's stumps. McCullum did not get a hand on it, Hansra was miles out.
ha, he backs away, Nathan follows him and Bagai whacks it straight back to the left of the bowler for a couple. Btw, Ponting is out in Bangalore.
moves away to the leg side and hits down the ground for another single. Bagai is now down for the count with a horrible onset of cramps. Hot and humid day in Bombay, not helping his health one bit.
Hansra gets to 50 with a nudge to square leg. Nice doughty innings. It's a real pity Canada lost the plot with the ball.

that's the end of a fine innings from Bagai. He's succumbed to the conditions as much as the bowling. He's barely able to stand, and wanted to get to his 100 with big shots. He again backs away to the leg side, looking to whack over the off side. Thin outside edge. Bagai c McCullum b McCullum.
slow offcutter on middle and off, driven down the ground without timing for a single
full on off, Cheema leans into the drive but finds cover
Cheema is away, clipping the on-drive past mid on for a single
over-pitched on the stumps, worked to the leg side for a single.
Cheema gets a single, playing down the ground for one
Hansra drives into the off side for another single to end the over

another one bites the dust. No fireworks from Cheema as he looks to guide a short ball on off stump to third man, and ends up guiding it too fine. Baz dives away to his right and pouches it. Very good catch, that.
he can't get bat on the first ball, feeling outside the off and missing.
Davison is away with a smooth cover drive for four. Over-pitched on off stump, he just leans into it and sends it on its way with a wholesome stroke through the line.
slower ball, and short too, completely catches him napping as he comes down the track and looks to pull. It goes off the toe end of the bat towards point
whoa, floored by a slow bouncer at 117 kph, Davison can't spot it and goes down like a sack of potatoes as he tries to get out of the way.
now a bouncer like he means it, Davison has a flail at the pull shot and misses again
offcutter on off, Hansra presses forward and defends down the track
holds the length back on middle and off, played down the track carefully
length ball on off, played back down the bowler sedately. Canada seem to have decided to just bat this out.
this one slips onto the pads, and is nudged backward of square for another single
full outside off, defended solidly down the track
another offcutter ending on middle and leg, played off the front foot down the track. This is turning into one of the most pointless dawdles. Ever.

yorker first up from Oram, the batsman is in some strife as he tries to get the toes away from the line of fire. Bye taken on the leg side of the stumps. Canada's fitness is really plumbing new lows. Umpire Tarapore is helping Hansra stretch out as the physio trots out once again.
short of a length outside off, steered backward of point for a single
length ball on off stump, Rao pokes into the covers and nearly runs himself out as he tries a lazy single.
bouncer on off stump, he looks to pull and misses
fuller length on off stump, driven down the ground for a single
whoa, Rao's done a Ryder, walking across his stumps and lapping a length ball angling in over backward square leg for a boundary
attempted yorker tails into the pads and Davison can't connect with the flick
full toss outside off, he can't connect with the cover drive
yorker on off stump, Rao's running is a sight for sore eyes. He's dug this out to cover and taken off in his own roly-poly style for a single that was never there.
Davison cracks another cover drive with power and placement. Four more to the cause.
fuller ball on the stumps, driven down the ground for a single
bouncer, too short and called wide.

swipe and a miss. Comes in sharply from round the wicket and raps him on the pads as he looks to shovel across the line. The umpire turns down the lbw appeal and it is referred by the NZ team. Replays say it was going down the leg side.
Oram lands this well wide of off stump and it is carved over the covers for a couple
Rao gets a single this time, tipping through the leg side
Davison continues to struggle against the bouncer, somehow manages to get bat on a late attempt at the shot.
bouncer aimed at the head, Rao wisely under it
Rao's holed out. Slow offcutter banged in short, he looks to biff it over midwicket and ends up playing straight to long on
poorly timed by Davison, lofts the on-drive almost straight down long on's throat. So poorly played, it did not carry.
aha, Umpire Tarapore gets into the batsman's path as he tries to scramble back into the crease as Davison flicks to midwicket. They try a single and abort the plans.
whoa, super yorker completely through the batsman who thinks he is bowled but it tails in so sharply to miss the stumps and fly to fine leg
and now a bouncer, Davison definitely doesn't like them. He tries to pull in ungainly fashion and misses
fuller on off stump, driven into the covers for a single
full toss on leg stump, flicked to midwicket for a single
full length ball on off stump, driven solidly to mid off

Davison has run himself out in clumsy fashion as the Royal Canadian Air Farce carries on. He gets a yorker on the pads, glances to the leg side and then trots half the way, before deciding to walk down the pitch. The throw came in from McCullum, on the sly, and broke the stumps before he reached his crease. Sleeping tortoises would have made it. Even if they were walking backwards. Davison keeps walking to the pavilion.
almost another hole-out. Slow loft, lacking in intent, into the leg side, but it lands safe
short ball, he's smacked the pull shot with some vengeance and its flown away to the square leg boundary
Baidwan escapes, looking to swipe out to the leg side and gets a thick outside edge that Baz can't collect as he jumps away to his right.
short ball, he goes for the pull and gets it down to deep backward square leg for a single
full toss on off, driven down to long on for another single.
Southee finally has a wicket. Rejoice if he's in your Fantasy team. Full toss on off stump, driven cleanly, but straight into mid off's hands
over-pitched on off, driven fluidly to mid off
another yorker, the batsman does well to save the toes and dig it out
another one very full on the stumps, driven without timing to the off side
back of a length on off stump, defended to the off side
slower ball from Oram outside off, cut backward of point for a single
another outside edge escapes McCullum, seems to be one of the best scoring areas. Hansra looks to carve expansively over the off side and gets it very fine for four
short ball, Hansra is cramped into the pull and the top edge flies to the left of McCullum to fine leg
yorker on the stumps, dug out to the leg side for a single
slow bouncer, called a wide for height.
another outside edge through third man. Another four. The theme of Canada's innings.

will they refer this? Huge lbw appeal as Southee raps the toes with another yorker. They are referring it after Tarapore turned the appeal down. This is going to be tough to call. The ball tailed in around middle and leg, Chohan was back in the crease as he looked to play across the line. Did it take the inside edge? Well it was heading well down the leg side in any case. Not out.
fuller ball on off stump, it is dug out to the off side
full toss on off stump, driven without timing into the covers
the Canadian third man dinks continue unabated. McCullum has dived to his right more often than ever before today. This one passes him and they get a single.
full toss from round the wicket, defended solidly to the off side
over-pitched on the pads, flicked straight to midwicket
Chohan pumps him through midwicket with disdain. He jumps out, reaches the pitch and whips through midwicket.
he goes two better this time. Does seem like they have left the onslaught for too late. Another full ball on leg stump, Chohan gets to the flight and dumps him all the way over midwicket
again full, Chohan powerfully flicks through midwicket for one more
digs out a full ball to long on for one
Chohan sends the ball in the same region, getting a single in the same region.
another six. Horrible finish for anyone who has Nathan in their Fantasy XI! Hansra plonks the front foot forward and across before thwacking him majestically over long off.
short ball outside off, cross-batted down to long off for one more
well outside off, called a wide
this one nips in off the seam and it nudged to midwicket for a single
Canada are ending with a sting here, Chohan lines up a full and slow ball on off stump, hanging back in the crease and going straight down the ground. He bisects long on and long off for four more.
Chohan's merry ways come to an end as Ryder keeps it slightly short of driving length and Chohan holes out to cover.
back of a length outside off, steered to short third man
Hansra has ended unbeaten, Ryder hasn't delivered any of those ten no balls and NZ have won in slightly lesser convincing fashion than seemed possible at one stage.
